<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4295" src="http://www.yempo-solutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Outsourcing-to-the-Philippines-Everything-You-Need-to-Know.jpg" alt="Outsourcing-to-the-Philippines-Everything-You-Need-to-Know" width="900" height="444" />
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Technology Driven Business Progress</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">With the growth in technological advancements and proliferation of the internet and its usage in most households, the world is now becoming a global village. Distances and international boundaries are not as significant as they were a few years ago. Business industry is one of the most drastically affected sectors of society. With so many easier, faster, and more efficient modes of communication, competition in the business world is at its peak. In such circumstances, looking out for ways to maximize profits and meet the goals of organizations is very difficult. Companies worldwide are looking out for cheaper and more effective ways of cutting down costs and outperforming their competitors to grab a larger portion of the market segment.</p>

<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Outsourcing Is a Growing Phenomenon</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">One very popularly used strategy to cut down expenses and production costs is Business Process Outsourcing or BPO. It allows business entities to reduce their production costs and infrastructure expenses by utilizing the cheaper resources and skills available in different geographic locations. According to business experts, the long-term future growth and economic stability of a company is dependent on its ability to sustain a consistent income generation process and develop new customers and products. Targeting the labor markets of the international world helps companies to create a profitable balance between product quality and reduced production costs. This is the major benefit of outsourcing your processes to other vendors located in different countries.</p>

<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>The Philippines</strong><strong> as an Outsourcing Partner</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">For any business entity, there are a large number of countries that offer favorable conditions for outsourcing or BPO. Selecting the right vendor and the appropriate geographic location for hiring your outsourcing partner can be challenging, as well as critical for future success. Among the large number of countries which are known for offering outsourcing services to business entities worldwide, the Â Philippines is one of the top-rated countries. It is listed in the 5 best of the worldâ€™s greatest and most beneficial outsourcing destinations across the globe.</p>

<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Reasons for Selecting the Philippines for Outsourcing</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Business outsourcing to the Philippines has been growing at a fast rate in the past few years. Today there are a very large number of business organizations which have invested in this growing economy. But why is this destination chosen by so many international companies for their outsourcing needs? Let us look at some of the reasons that make the Philippines top rated for outsourcing business:</p>

<ul>
 	<li>The Philippines is a country that has one of the highest literacy rates in the world. According to many resources, this rate is nearly 97% which is higher than anywhere else in the world.</li>
 	<li>Most Filipinos are well versed in the English language. It is widely spoken across the country and is considered one of their native languages. For companies outsourcing to the Philippines this is efficient; as it is something they have in common, English can be understood by both the partners. This is one of the major plus points for those looking for call center partnerships.</li>
 	<li>This country was an American colony from 1898 until Before that, the country had been under Spanish rule. As a result of this historical past, the countryâ€™s culture is closer to a western countriesâ€™ culture than that of its own geographic region.</li>
 	<li>Outsourcing to the Philippines is very common because of the large pool of labor in the country. According to estimates, there are more than ten million people already working in the metropolitan city of Manila alone. It is a densely populated country with the necessary infrastructure as well as the technological requirements needed for modern business operations.</li>
 	<li>In general, demographically the countryâ€™s inhabitants are considered to be friendly and hardworking, traits that are important for good employees.</li>
 	<li>Because of the number of workers and high population, the cost of labor is much cheaper in the Philippines than anywhere else in the region. Hence, outsourcing to the Philippines helps businesses to reduce costs without compromising quality.</li>
 	<li>People in the Philippines are hardworking and motivated. They are usually willing to work without time constraints. As a consequence, the difference in time between western countries and the Philippines is not a problem.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Summary</strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">So we see that outsourcing to the Philippines is becoming popular and widely accepted across the business industry in the western world. It is immensely beneficial for organizations and enables them to enhance their profitability by using the growing opportunities available in this country. It is not only advantageous for the business industry but it also provides new and better opportunities for the Filipinos in the country. For this reason, the government of the Philippines is very supportive of outsourcing projects and in some instances provides tax advantages for them.</p>
